To create a Discord bot using Discord.js v14 that has a single slash command (`/ban`) with a custom behavior, you need to follow these steps:

1. Set up your bot on the Discord Developer Portal.
2. Get your bot token.
3. Create a new project in your GitHub repository to house your bot code.
4. Clone the Discord.js v14 repository and set up the project.
5. Implement the /ban command with a custom behavior.

Here's a step-by-step guide with the code:

### 1. Set Up Your Bot on the Discord Developer Portal

1. Go to the [Discord Developer Portal](https://discord.com/developers/applications) and sign in.
2. Create a new application and bot.
3. Copy your bot token; you'll need it for the code.

### 2. Create a New Project on GitHub

1. Go to your GitHub account and create a new repository.
2. Clone the following repository into your GitHub repository:

```sh
git clone https://github.com/discord.js/discord.js-v14.git
cd discord.js-v14
```

### 3. Set Up the Project

1. Create a `package.json` file in the root of your project with the following content:

```json
{
  "name": "bot-name",
  "version": "v14",
  "main": "index.js",
  "scripts": {
    "start": "node index.js"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "discord.js": "^14.0.1"
  }
}
```

2. Create a `package-lock.json` file in the root of your project with the following content:

```json
{
  "name": "bot-name",
  "version": "v14.0.1",
  "description": "Discord.js v14 Bot",
  "main": "index.js",
  "dependencies": {
    "discord.js": "^14.0.1"
  }
}
```

### 4. Implement the Bot

1. Inside your `index.js` file, implement the bot with the /ban command:

```javascript
const { Client, Intents } = require('discord.js');
const client = new Client({ intents: [Intents.FLAGS.GUILD_MEMBER, Intents.FLAGS.GUILD_INVITE, Intents.FLAGS.GUILD_BAN] });

// Replace with your bot's token
const TOKEN = 'YOUR_BOT_TOKEN';

async function init() {
  await client.once('ready', () => {
    console.log('Bot is ready!');
  });
}

async function messageHandler(message, sender, sub) {
  const { command } = message;

  if (command === '/ban') {
    const target = command?.args[0];
    if (target) {
      await client.sendMessage(
        sub,
        await client.command(target),
        {
          type: 'ban',
          reason: 'Banned for <0.1 second.'
        }
      );
      client.stopCommand(command);
    } else {
      await client.sendMessage(
        sub,
        'You must specify a target',
      );
    }
  }

  await client.messageHandler(sub);
}

init();
```

### 5. Start the Bot

1. Run your bot using the following command:

```sh
node index.js
```

### 6. Interact with Your Bot

